 the map to the embedded subjectivity of GPS. Likewise, older concerns with geographic truth and objectivity have been upstaged by a new emphasis on simplicity, reliability, and convenience. After the Map shows how this change in geographic perspective is ultimately a transformation of the nature of territory, both social and political.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aUniversal transverse Mercator projection (Cartography). 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z97831107109840 cprintz978022633936840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226339535423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226339535/original  a978-3-11-071098-4  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles